The manuscript volume presents us with ample material for an examination of Erasmus' orthography. It appears that he uses the form -e far more commonly than -ae; which rarely occurs except as -e. In a few cases (ff. 213, 214, 219 νο.) in revising Erasmus adds a cedilla to an -e; but this is quite exceptional.
